14. Write a program to read a character until a * is encountered. Also count the number of 
uppercase, lowercase, and numbers entered by the users. 
Sample Input: 
Enter * to exitâ€¦ 
Enter any character: W 
Enter any character: d 
Enter any character: A 
Enter any character: G 
Enter any character: g 
Enter any character: H 
Enter any character: * 
Sample Output: 
Total count of lower case:2 
Total count of upper case:4 
Total count of numbers =0 

CODE: 
public class CountCharacters {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Hardcoded input sequence (like user typed them)
        char[] inputs = {'W', 'd', 'A', 'G', 'g', 'H', '*'};

        int lower = 0, upper = 0, digits = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < inputs.length; i++) {
            char ch = inputs[i];

            if (ch == '*') {
                break; // stop input
            }

            if (ch >= 'a' && ch <= 'z') {
                lower++;
            } else if (ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z') {
                upper++;
            } else if (ch >= '0' && ch <= '9') {
                digits++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println("Total count of lower case: " + lower);
        System.out.println("Total count of upper case: " + upper);
        System.out.println("Total count of numbers: " + digits);
    }
}
